            <title>[JDK-8308235] ThreadContainer registry accumulates weak refs</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8308235</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>This is memory leak / regression since JDK 19 due to the addition of the registry of thread containers. If you create lots of thread pools, don&#8217;t close them, let them be GC&#8217;ed, then the weak refs to these contains aren&amp;#39;t expunged from the registry. See analysis from Alexey Gavrilov here:&lt;br/&gt;
